  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-07-16",
    "date": "2021-08-24T23:58:46Z",
    "text": "Better Empowerment Now to Enhance Framework and Improve Treatments Act of 2021 or the BENEFIT Act of 2021\n\nThis bill requires the Food and Drug Administration (FDA) to consider relevant patient-focused drug development data, such as data from patient preference studies and patient-reported outcome data, in the risk-benefit assessment framework used in the process for approving new drugs.\n\nAfter a new drug application has been approved, the FDA's public statement about how it used patient experience data shall include a description of how such data was considered in the risk-benefit assessment framework."
  },
